HEADWORD: Kendal
<hw>Ken"dal</hw>. }</mhw> <def>A cloth colored green by dye obtained
from the woad-waxen, formerly used by Flemish weavers at
<etsep>Kendal</etsep>, in Westmoreland, England.</def> <rj><au>J. Smith
(Dict. Econ. Plants).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How couldst thou know these men in <qex>Kendal green</qex> ?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

